		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Aug 22nd 2:30 PM2001 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=99833872894268&num=2&page=0&post=1&replyto=99850503731961"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=99850503731961></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Basic rule for stacking questions is this: If it has a buffing icon, like, say, Anthem, then it will not stack with multiple bards. It is an effect, like any other buff, just with a short duration. Just like you can't stack a shammy str buff with the same one from another shammy. The mana song "stacks" because it isn't a buff or effect. Every time you play it i.e. every time you get the message "Your mind clears" it restores a bit of mana. It is instant, rather than an effect. It gives the illusion of being a stacked buff if multiple bard play it, though the real effect is just more bards hitting the party every three seconds or so with an instant mana regen, so even then, it isn't really stacking.<br /><br />Cidol Wrathdealer<br />35 Bard of Karana<br />Drinal</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
